        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(ui): inline rename in the in-chat session picker",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- **Problem:** The in-chat session picker only lets users *switch* sessions. Renaming still requires the admin \"Sessions\" tab, which is cumbersome when juggling several parallel, topic-specific chats — exactly the friction reported in #54397.\r\n- **Change:** Add a per-row inline rename affordance to the chat session-picker popover. An edit button on each row opens an inline input seeded with the current label; Enter / Save commits, Escape / Cancel discards.\r\n- **Reuse, no new write path:** Commit goes through the existing self-refreshing `patchSession(state, key, {label})` flow (the same `sessions.patch` + `loadSessions()` path the admin Sessions tab already uses). Empty/whitespace input clears the label via `normalizeOptionalString`, matching admin-tab semantics exactly.\r\n- **Out of scope (intentional):** chat slash-commands for naming (`/name`, `/new --name`, `/sessions`), switching sessions from text channels, and any LLM auto-suggest. Those are planned as separate, smaller PRs.\r\n- **Success:** Users can rename a session without leaving the chat; behavior and validation are identical to the existing admin rename.\r\n\r\n## Linked context\r\n\r\nRelated #54397, #85502\r\n\r\nThis is the small \"header/sidebar shortcut\" that maintainers explicitly invited as a separate polish request when closing #85502 (the admin-tab rename shipped there). It also advances the chat-native session-management UX discussed in #54397. I deliberately did not put `Closes #` because neither issue is a 1:1 match — happy to add one if a maintainer prefers.\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\r\n\r\n- **Behavior addressed:** Rename a session inline from the in-chat session picker (open picker → edit icon on a row → type → Enter/Save), including clear-on-empty and cancel.\r\n- **Real environment tested:** Component/DOM behavior via the project's vitest + jsdom harness exercising the real `renderChatSessionSelect` render path (no mocked component internals; only the `controllers/sessions` boundary is mocked, consistent with the existing picker tests in the same file).\r\n- **Exact commands run after this patch:**\r\n  - `cd ui && pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.config.ts src/ui/views/chat.test.ts` → 69 passed\r\n  - `pnpm tsgo:test:ui` → clean\r\n  - `pnpm ui:i18n:check` → clean\r\n  - `oxlint` + `oxfmt --check` on changed files → 0 errors, formatted\r\n- **Evidence after fix (terminal capture):**\r\n\r\n  ```\r\n  ✓ src/ui/views/chat.test.ts (69 tests)\r\n    chat session controls\r\n      ✓ renames a chat session from the picker via patchSession\r\n      ✓ clears a whitespace-only chat session rename to remove the label\r\n      ✓ cancels a chat session rename without patching\r\n      ✓ discards an in-progress rename when the picker closes\r\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\r\n       Tests  69 passed (69)\r\n  ```\r\n\r\n- **Observed result after fix:** The rename trigger enters inline edit mode for the targeted row; commit calls `patchSession` with the normalized label (or `null` to clear) and the list refreshes; cancel/close discards the draft and leaves the label unchanged.\r\n- **What was not tested:** End-to-end against a live running gateway + browser; visual styling on a real device.\r\n- **Proof limitations / environment constraints:** This was developed in a headless dev environment without a running OpenClaw gateway/browser, so I could not capture a live UI screenshot/recording. Proof is therefore the DOM-level vitest run that drives the actual render function and asserts the real `patchSession` call and state transitions, plus typecheck/i18n/lint. Glad to add a screen capture if a maintainer can point me at a quick way to run the UI here, or if a reviewer with a live setup can confirm.\r\n\r\n## Tests and validation\r\n\r\n- Added 4 focused tests in `ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts` under \"chat session controls\": commit via Enter, clear-on-whitespace via Save, cancel via Escape, and discard-on-close (regression guard so closing the picker mid-edit cannot leak a stale rename/draft).\r\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:ui`, `pnpm ui:i18n:check`, oxlint and oxfmt all green on the changes.\r\n\r\n## Risk checklist\r\n\r\n- **User-visible behavior change?** Yes — a new rename control in the chat session picker.\r\n- **Config/env/migration change?** No.\r\n- **Security/auth/secrets/network/tool-exec change?** No new write path or permission surface; reuses the existing `sessions.patch` flow already used by the admin rename.\r\n- **Highest-risk area:** ARIA structure — rows are now wrapped in a `<div>` to host the rename button. Mitigation: wrappers are marked `role=\"presentation\"` so options remain owned by the `listbox`. Note: this picker was already a loose listbox (button options, no roving tabindex); a deeper `list`/`listitem` refactor is intentionally left out of scope.\r\n- **Mitigation:** Label normalization/clear semantics are delegated to the same helper as the admin tab; commit uses the existing self-refreshing controller; rename state is cleared on every picker-close path (covered by a test).\r\n\r\n## Current review state\r\n\r\n- **Next action:** Maintainer review of the UX placement and the ARIA `role=\"presentation\"` approach.\r\n- **Waiting on:** CI; optional live-UI screenshot if required (see proof limitations).\r\n- **Bot/reviewer comments addressed:** N/A (initial submission).\r\n",
